answers.body_markdown:
While converting a Java code to JSP format you need to keep the following points in mind:

 1. Imports
 - `import java.util.Arrays;` -&gt; `&lt;%@page import=&quot;java.util.Arrays&quot;%&gt;`

 2. Main method - starting point of your JSP
 - Java code needs to be within `&lt;% ... %&gt;`

 3. Other code - such as sub classes/methods
 - Java code needs to be within `&lt;%! ... %&gt;`

 4. Printing
 - `System.out` can be replaced with the `out` which is an instance of JspWriter class.

Example -&gt;

**Java:**
```
    import java.util.ArrayList;
    import java.util.List;
    
    class Scratch
    {
    	public static void main(String[] args)
    	{
    		List&lt;Integer&gt; values = new ArrayList&lt;&gt;();
    		values.add(12);
    		values.add(2);
    		values.add(33);
    		System.out.println(&quot;Sum = &quot; + getSum(values));
    	}
    
    	/*
    		Method returns sum of elements of an array
    	 */
    	private static int getSum(List&lt;Integer&gt; values)
    	{
    		int sum = 0;
    		for (int i : values)
    		{
    			sum += i;
    		}
    		return sum;
    	}
    }
```

**JSP:**

```
    &lt;%-- Imports --%&gt;
    &lt;%@page import=&quot;java.util.ArrayList&quot;%&gt;
    &lt;%@page import=&quot;java.util.List&quot;%&gt;
    
    &lt;%-- Main --%&gt;
    &lt;%
    		List&lt;Integer&gt; values = new ArrayList&lt;&gt;();
    		values.add(12);
    		values.add(2);
    		values.add(33);
    		out.println(&quot;Sum = &quot; + getSum(values));
    %&gt;
    
